Two houses were on Thursday torched and several people injured after a group of youth from Ofunyu area reportedly attacked residents of the nearby Otera village in Kolwa Central, Kisumu County. This, according to sources, was in retaliation to a recent incident where a middle-aged man and his girlfriend from Ofunyu were allegedly attacked in Otera. The said man reportedly succumbed to his injuries following the Monday attack, eliciting the anger of his peers in Ofunyu. The group of youth from Ofunyu is said to have stormed Otera village seeking to retaliate against those who had attacked the deceased. Armed with crude weapons, they ransacked houses and torched two, including one belonging to a village elder, leaving some people injured as others fled for safety. One person who was seriously injured during the attack has since been rushed to the Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referral Hospital (JOOTRH)Â for treatment. Also Read: Otera village residents now want police to beef up security in the area and bring the suspects to book since they vowed to come back in the night and torch more houses. Nyalunya sub-location Assistant Chief Boniface Modho confirmed the incident saying police have already kicked off investigations. Video Of The Day: | SUCCESS AND AFTER | Tracking the progress made by students who topped KCSE in past years